			<div id="text-21674986" class="p">
			olsmeister writes <i>"A <a href="http://www.bitcoin.org/">Bitcoin</a> user allegedly has had <a href="http://www.pcworld.com/article/230377/worlds_first_virtual_heist_bitcoin_user_loses_500000.html">$500,000 worth of Bitcoins stolen</a> from him.  A hacker supposedly gained access to the user's home computer and managed to get the user's wallet.dat file, which contained the cryptographic keys that allowed him to drain the user's balance."</i>

