	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_36462696">The problems here are threefold in the normal bitcoin client:
<ol>
<li>The wallet in bitcoin is not encrypted. It's plaintext.</li><li>The wallet is stored in a predictable location, %APPDATA%/bitcoin/wallet.dat</li><li>There is nothing tying the wallet to a particular machine (e.g. encryption).</li><span class="substr"> </span></ol><p>
As such all one would need to do is steal the wallet, either through a trojan or possibly even a browser exploit (which guessed the APPDATA path by trying someone's likely login id) and that is that. Their copy of the wallet can initiate th</p></div>
	</div>

