			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_36463420"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_36463420">And all transfers from your savings account wallet to your spending wallet should be done on an offline computer so that your savings account wallet is never on a computer connected to the internet, otherwise you risk a digital intruder keylogging your passphrase to decrypt the savings account wallet, or just copying it while you have it decrypted or copying the unencrypted file from bits on the drive (where you erased it, but didn't shred it because you probably use a journaling filesystem).</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_36463420">

</div>
