	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_36462186"><p>This thread was on Reddit 2 days ago. Here's the link: http://www.reddit.com/r/geek/comments/hzrcc/bitcoin_user_loses_25k_bitcoins_when_his_machine/</p><p>To summarise:<br>
&nbsp; * it could've never been $500k, that's purely theoretical. In practise it would be worth far less.<br>
&nbsp; * "allinvain" is a true idiot. He was keeping the coins on his main computer which had a virus on it. He was browsing the web and IRCing with it. He found the trojan the night before, had seen that his payout address was changed to another and then to fix this he "changed it back" and went to sleep. He then "moved [his wallet] to a Ubuntu linux vmware install. On the same machine."<br>
&nbsp; * It's probably a hoax</p></div>
