	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_36461888"><p>If I understand the technology, if he were to try to sell bitcoins from a backup<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.dat, the bitcoin network would reject the transaction as fraudulent saying that he no longer owned the coins he is trying to transfer.</p><p>The immediate transfer would go through, and over the next 10 minutes both parties would recieve thousands of "I don't agree that this transfer is valid, invalidate it" messages from other nodes on the bitcoin p2p network.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_36461888">

